          <h2>Install Unity</h2>
          <p>Ready to get Started?</p>
          
          <p>First, let’s go to Unity’s <a href= "https://unity3d.com/">website</a>. 
          You can also click on <a href= "https://unity3d.com/">https://unity3d.com/</a>
          to take you there. You should make sure that the page opens up in a
          new tab so that way you can look at this page and at Unity’s page at 
          the same time. </p>
          
          <p>You should see (t1s1i1). We are now going to click on Get Unity.</p>
          
          <p>After doing so, Unity will give you four different “plans” to 
          choose from. All of the plans except for Personal charge money. 
          The reason why is because they offer other benefits that the Personal 
          plan does not come with. They also are for more experienced users and 
          for organizations and companies. For us, the Personal version will work 
          the best. Click on the green Try Personal button. </p>
          
          <p>Awesome!</p>
          
          <p>Now here is where things can get a little bit confusing. 
          First off, do you have a Mac or a PC? A PC is usually any 
          computer that is not a Mac. </p>
          
          <p>Now, you will need to make sure that your computer 
          meets all of the minimum requirements for Unity to work. If you don’t 
          meet the minimum requirements, then Unity may not install or it may install,
          but it will run super slowly. </p>
          
        </div>
