      <!-- Content-->
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="inner">
          <h3 class="major">PC</h3>
          <p>For PCs, your computer needs to have at least Windows 7. 
          If you have Windows 8 or 10, then you are fine. </p>
          <p>You need to also make sure that your Graphics card has 
          at least DX9 with shader model 3.0 or be at least DX11. </p>
          <p>Now this is a lot of confusing information. What does DX9 
          mean? What does shader model mean? You can check out Here 
          (link to resources page with more information) to learn more about it. 
          For now, understand that this information just means how nice and
          pretty your computer can make things look. </p>
          
          <p>To check what type of DX you have, do the following. 
          (This will differ on whether the person has 7, 8. 8.1, or 10, I 
          cant do images of 7 or 8 unfortunately)</p>
          
          <h4> For Windows 10:</h4>
          <li>Click on Cortana.</li>
          <li>In Type To Search, type in Run and hit Enter.</li>
          <li>Type in dxdiag in the box and then click on OK</li>
          <li>Look for DirectX Version and It will tell you what version of 
              DX you have (it will say DirectX 12 for example).</li>
          <li>When you are done, click on Exit.</li> 
          <p>And there you go!</p>

          <h3 class="major">Mac</h3>
